"암스테르담":{en:{description:"Amsterdam is a canal-laced city of world-class museums, cycling culture, historic merchant houses, and liberal attitudes.",spots:{"안네 프랑크의 집":{"name":null,"desc":"The secret annex where Anne Frank hid during WWII and wrote her diary. One of Europe's most moving museums."},"반고흐 미술관":{"name":null,"desc":"World's largest collection of Van Gogh works, including Sunflowers and The Bedroom."},"국립미술관(레이크스뮤지엄)":{"name":null,"desc":"Netherlands' greatest museum housing Rembrandt's Night Watch and Vermeer's Milkmaid."},"요르단 지구":{"name":null,"desc":"Amsterdam's most charming neighborhood of narrow canals, independent shops, and cozy brown cafés."}}}},
