"프라하":{en:{description:"Prague is the 'City of a Hundred Spires' — a fairy-tale capital of Gothic, Baroque, and Art Nouveau architecture.",spots:{"프라하 성":{"name":null,"desc":"World's largest ancient castle complex, home to St. Vitus Cathedral and stunning city views."},"카를교":{"name":null,"desc":"14th-century Gothic bridge lined with 30 baroque statues, connecting Old Town to the castle quarter."},"구시가지 광장":{"name":null,"desc":"Prague's medieval heart with the Astronomical Clock, Týn Church, and colorful baroque buildings."},"유대인 지구":{"name":null,"desc":"Historic Jewish quarter with six synagogues, the Old Jewish Cemetery, and a moving Kafka connection."}}}},
